lobbying_activities: [{'general_issue_code': 'MAR', 'general_issue_code_display': 'Marine/Maritime/Boating/Fisheries', 'description': 'Support for inclusion in FY 2021 Energy & Water Appropriations Bills report language encouraging the Army Corps of Engineers to better assess water quality impacts on Gulf of Mexico oysters of navigation and coastal restoration projects and where feasible to mitigate any negative impacts on area oyster reefs. Monitor funding and development of Gulf coastal restoration, flood control and navigation projects. The E&W FY2021 Appropriations Bill: Sections dealing with the Bureau of Reclamation and the Army Corps, issues associated with ocean water desalination and water infrastructure development. Competitive Grant Programs, and funding for environmental infrastructure accounts., The FY2021 Agriculture Appropriations Bill, Sections dealing with the Department of Agriculture Natural Resources Conservation Service:
Grant Programs. Federal grants for water related infrastructure. National Infrastructure Bank Issues. WIFIA issues regarding federal tax exempt bonds and the percentage of a project that can qualify for WIFIA funding. Issues associated with how much of
a project can be funded through WIFIA. Federal budgetary, regulatory and environmental issues affecting Ocean Water Desalination Projects. EPA State Revolving Loan Fund Programs. The Doheny Ocean Water Desalination Project in Orange County, California. Water issues and project deauthorization related issues in the 2016 WRDA Bill, S.612. Issues associated with Section 5039 of the 2007 WRDA Bill. 
The California drought, Western States drought, and the Drought Implementation Plan. Wildfire funding. Federal tax issues associated with turf removal and water conservation programs.
